Here are some basic examples of how to apply CSS blend modes:

1. Multiplying an image with a background:

```CSS
.background {
  background-image: url('background-image.jpg');
}

.image {
  background-image: url('image.jpg');
  mix-blend-mode: multiply;
}
```

2. Overlapping two images with different blend modes:

```CSS
.image1 {
  background-image: url('image1.jpg');
}

.image2 {
  background-image: url('image2.jpg');
  mix-blend-mode: overlay;
}
```

3. Applying a blend mode to text:

```CSS
.text {
  font-size: 5rem;
  color: white;
  background-color: black;
  mix-blend-mode: screen;
}
```

4. Combining a blend mode with a hover effect:

```CSS
.image {
  background-image: url('image.jpg');
  mix-blend-mode: screen;
  transition: all 0.5s ease;
}

.image:hover {
  mix-blend-mode: multiply;
}
```

Remember, the possibilities are endless when it comes to CSS blend modes. Play around with different colors, images, text, and backgrounds to create unique and visually stunning effects.

